00:11:57,940 --> 00:12:00,120
A person's energy is limited,

294
00:12:00,639 --> 00:12:02,159
so you must spend it

295
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,539
on those most worth it.

296
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:05,960
In the future, really,

297
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:08,059
the people who need to write

298
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,440
are the ones with

299
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,120
social status.

300
00:12:10,340 --> 00:12:11,100
Take, for instance,

301
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:12,759
those two kids from just now.

302
00:12:13,539 --> 00:12:15,080
You've got to read the room in life.

303
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:17,379
The ones worth grooming, teach them harder.

304
00:12:17,899 --> 00:12:19,600
The rest, just getting by is enough.

305
00:12:20,679 --> 00:12:22,200
Your kid's the same, actually.

306
00:12:24,659 --> 00:12:26,200
What kind of person

307
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,000
he becomes in the future,

308
00:12:27,639 --> 00:12:28,360
it all depends on

309
00:12:28,379 --> 00:12:29,419
what kind of father

310
00:12:29,419 --> 00:12:30,299
you find for him.

311
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:32,899
That's the key part.

312
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:35,620
I've truly been blinded by a single leaf,

313
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,759
missing the whole mountain.

314
00:12:38,899 --> 00:12:40,480
All I have left now is admiration for you.

315
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:43,279
Xiaofang,

316
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:45,220
hearing you say that

317
00:12:45,759 --> 00:12:46,580
really warms my heart.

318
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,759
It shows you understand what I'm saying.

319
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:52,840
I just realized

320
00:12:52,899 --> 00:12:54,100
what you really resemble.

321
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:55,139
Come.

322
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,620
You're just like this sheet of rice paper.

323
00:13:01,779 --> 00:13:03,240
Full of spirit,

324
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:05,519
but still completely blank.

325
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:07,259
Once you're with me,

326
00:13:07,379 --> 00:13:08,879
I'll shape you

327
00:13:08,919 --> 00:13:09,620
in every possible way.

328
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,059
Like that blue outfit you're wearing today,

329
00:13:12,059 --> 00:13:13,179
I suggest you never wear it again.

330
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:13,919
It doesn't suit you.

331
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,500
I want you to wear more white,

332
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:17,960
so you look

333
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,039
pure.

334
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:20,559
Boss Hao,

335
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:23,240
I'd really love to learn from you,

336
00:13:24,659 --> 00:13:26,320
but I already have a teacher.

337
00:13:27,639 --> 00:13:30,379
And which master are you studying under?

338
00:13:31,299 --> 00:13:32,220
Ever since I can remember,

339
00:13:32,299 --> 00:13:33,360
I've been studying under

340
00:13:33,519 --> 00:13:35,779
the famous Master Yang Fanzhu,

341
00:13:35,779 --> 00:13:36,460
learning about the world.

342
00:13:38,519 --> 00:13:39,899
Master Yang is renowned.

343
00:13:40,639 --> 00:13:41,799
Surely you know him?

344
00:13:43,159 --> 00:13:43,940
Of course, of course.

345
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:44,879
Of course.

346
00:13:44,899 --> 00:13:45,840
Master Yang Fanzhu, of course.

347
00:13:46,019 --> 00:13:46,940
We know each other well.

348
00:13:47,659 --> 00:13:48,080
Right.

349
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:50,500
Master Yang's calligraphy is very famous.

350
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:51,000
Of course.

351
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:52,259
Then let me write something

352
00:13:52,259 --> 00:13:53,639
and you give me some pointers.

353
00:13:54,519 --> 00:13:55,500
Sure, sure, sure.

354
00:13:57,899 --> 00:13:58,399
Lay out the paper.

355
00:13:58,940 --> 00:13:59,320
Here.

356
00:14:05,799 --> 00:14:06,440
Which brush do you use?

357
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:10,059
I learned grand freehand style from Master Yang.

358
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:10,919
Use that big one.

359
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:12,659
So bold.

360
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,039
Come, students.

361
00:14:14,539 --> 00:14:15,299
Come on, everyone over here.

362
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:17,500
Let's study the grand freehand style.

363
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:15,879
Why did she write "daddy"?

364
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,000
Xiaofang was being sarcastic.

365
00:15:18,019 --> 00:15:19,779
That boss was so full of "daddy energy."

366
00:15:20,559 --> 00:15:21,779
What's "daddy energy"?

367
00:15:22,259 --> 00:15:23,460
You don't even know "daddy energy"?

368
00:15:24,559 --> 00:15:24,960
You, you...

369
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:26,539
Why do you fold planes like this now?

370
00:15:26,539 --> 00:15:27,539
Can that even fly far?

371
00:15:27,919 --> 00:15:28,639
Grandpa will fold one for you.

372
00:15:28,639 --> 00:15:29,480
The kind of plane we played with back in the day.

373
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,899
That's how the teacher taught us.

374
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:31,820
Just listen to Grandpa.

375
00:15:33,919 --> 00:15:34,799
This "daddy energy"...

376
00:15:34,799 --> 00:15:36,600
means not respecting others.

377
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,879
Always thinking you're the best,

378
00:15:38,899 --> 00:15:39,720
the greatest.

379
00:15:39,799 --> 00:15:41,220
Wishing everyone in the world

380
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,279
would have to listen to him.

381
00:15:43,539 --> 00:15:44,220
Keep it down.

382
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,259
So Xiaofang wasn't into him then.

383
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:50,899
Of course she wasn't.

384
00:15:51,059 --> 00:15:52,659
Xiaofang has high standards.

385
00:15:52,899 --> 00:15:53,559
At the very least,

386
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,419
he'd have to be like me, your son.

387
00:15:57,159 --> 00:15:58,320
You're really something.

388
00:15:58,659 --> 00:15:59,600
I'm a master.

389
00:16:00,039 --> 00:16:01,480
Great teachers raise great students, right?

390
00:16:03,139 --> 00:16:04,659
If you don't agree, just don't agree.

391
00:16:05,059 --> 00:16:07,019
No need to mess with the guy, right?

392
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:08,740
Auntie,

393
00:16:08,779 --> 00:16:09,620
you have no idea.

394
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:11,240
The way he kept bragging himself up,

395
00:16:12,059 --> 00:16:12,879
so full of himself.

396
00:16:13,299 --> 00:16:13,919
If he hadn't been putting on airs,

397
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:14,919
would I have treated him like that?

398
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:16,960
Enough is enough.

399
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,279
I know a lot of people

400
00:16:19,299 --> 00:16:20,620
are lining up to date you,

401
00:16:21,179 --> 00:16:22,159
but you have to be careful

402
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,820
about your own reputation.

403
00:16:24,019 --> 00:16:24,720
Don't go treating yourself

404
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,960
like some big superstar.

405
00:16:26,299 --> 00:16:27,340
I didn't.

406
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,019
Why wouldn't she be a superstar?

407
00:16:29,759 --> 00:16:30,759
In this county now,

408
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:31,820
guys looking

409
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,179
for a good wife are everywhere.

410
00:16:33,919 --> 00:16:35,519
Even with money, it's hard to find a wife.

411
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:37,299
Our Xiaofang

412
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:38,299
is basically

413
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,720
a superstar on the dating scene.

414
00:16:40,519 --> 00:16:42,159
Son, you need to watch out.

415
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,500
The more suitors she has,

416
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,159
the higher her standards get.

417
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:46,899
You've got to do something,

418
00:16:47,179 --> 00:16:48,279
sweet-talk her back.

419
00:16:50,419 --> 00:16:51,519
You hear me?

420
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:52,860
I got it, I got it, enough already.

421
00:16:55,940 --> 00:16:56,340
Brother Hu.

422
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,399
No, wait, Uncle Hu.

423
00:16:57,639 --> 00:16:58,600
Let me get that for you.

424
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,460
You take a break.

425
00:16:59,759 --> 00:17:00,399
Yeah yeah, Uncle Hu.

426
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:01,039
Want some water?

427
00:17:01,179 --> 00:17:01,899
I just brewed some tea.

428
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:02,919
Uncle Hu, have you eaten?

429
00:17:03,039 --> 00:17:04,160
Let's grab a bite together later.

430
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,579
They're all calling me uncle?

431
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,200
Uncle Hu, come on.

432
00:17:16,259 --> 00:17:16,940
Come on, Uncle Hu.

433
00:17:23,940 --> 00:17:24,319
Uncle.

434
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:25,859
What do you think of me?

435
00:17:27,259 --> 00:17:28,019
What do you mean?

436
00:17:28,819 --> 00:17:29,960
I'm not bad-looking, right?

437
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:31,140
Could you go for me?

438
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:33,579
What if Uncle Hu did go for you?

439
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:34,660
Marry you or something?

440
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:35,319
Exactly.

441
00:17:35,740 --> 00:17:36,519
What are you all fooling around for?

442
00:17:37,559 --> 00:17:38,119
Get back to work.

443
00:17:38,799 --> 00:17:39,400
Go, go, go.

444
00:17:41,099 --> 00:17:41,579
Little Lu,

445
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:44,980
these buddies of yours,

446
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,599
why are they all calling me uncle?

447
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:48,420
What's going on?

448
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,000
Uncle Hu,

449
00:17:50,539 --> 00:17:51,079
you've worked hard.

450
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,940
Why are you calling me uncle too?

451
00:17:55,519 --> 00:17:57,339
Actually, I should be calling you uncle.

452
00:17:58,059 --> 00:17:59,200
I'm not even thirty yet.

453
00:18:00,559 --> 00:18:02,259
About the same age as Xiaofang.

454
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:14,319
This is for you.

455
00:18:16,759 --> 00:18:17,500
Thank you.

456
00:18:18,359 --> 00:18:19,200
You're really skilled.

457
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:21,880
My family are woodcarvers by tradition.

458
00:18:22,539 --> 00:18:23,680
Originally, we used to

459
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,220
build palaces for the emperor.

460
00:18:26,220 --> 00:18:26,839
Don't worry.

461
00:18:27,099 --> 00:18:28,359
If we really end up together,

462
00:18:28,779 --> 00:18:30,279
I'll treat this child well.

463
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,779
Raise them as my own, for sure.

464
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,380
Doesn't matter if it's a boy or girl.

465
00:18:33,460 --> 00:18:34,079
When they grow up,

466
00:18:34,119 --> 00:18:35,559
I'll pass this craft down to them too.

467
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:37,880
Passing it down is a good thing.

468
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,160
But it also depends on the child's wishes.

469
00:18:40,660 --> 00:18:41,599
Yeah, right.

470
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,819
We'll have more kids later anyway.

471
00:18:45,359 --> 00:18:46,160
If they don't like it,

472
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,579
I'll pass it to our own kids.

473
00:18:50,059 --> 00:18:51,619
Lu, you're really thinking far ahead.

474
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:52,700
Xiaofang,

475
00:18:53,220 --> 00:18:54,559
there's one thing I really like about you,

476
00:18:54,599 --> 00:18:55,180
and it's especially important.

477
00:18:55,559 --> 00:18:57,140
You're pregnant, but

478
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,680
you still hike and work the fields just fine.

479
00:18:59,119 --> 00:19:00,579
Means you're healthy and can bear kids well.

480
00:19:01,619 --> 00:19:02,740
If we get married,

481
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:03,940
we've gotta hurry and have our own.

482
00:19:04,059 --> 00:19:05,440
I really love kids.

483
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:06,779
Let's have five or six.

484
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,619
Five or six? Can you support them?

485
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:09,619
Of course I can.

486
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:11,420
All the money I earn from now on,

487
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:12,339
I'll hand it all over to you.

488
00:19:16,519 --> 00:19:17,980
Lu, you love kids.

489
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:18,859
I love kids too.

490
00:19:19,259 --> 00:19:20,279
You want five or six kids.

491
00:19:20,279 --> 00:19:21,460
I want five or six kids too.

492
00:19:21,940 --> 00:19:22,519
So here's the deal.

493
00:19:22,759 --> 00:19:23,640
Why don't we just

494
00:19:23,660 --> 00:19:24,680
have a whole basketball team?

495
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,099
How about it?

496
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:28,220
We don't need that many.

497
00:19:28,559 --> 00:19:29,480
Not that many. Look,

498
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:30,819
a basketball team with subs

499
00:19:30,819 --> 00:19:31,839
is only twelve.

500
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,220
I won't do anything else.

501
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:35,500
I'll just have kids all day long.

502
00:19:35,819 --> 00:19:37,119
You'll hire me nannies and maids.

503
00:19:37,559 --> 00:19:38,259
Let me think.

504
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,019
Once the kids grow up,

505
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,900
each one needs a house in town.

506
00:19:42,099 --> 00:19:43,819
Prices in our town these days

507
00:19:44,319 --> 00:19:45,160
aren't that high.

508
00:19:45,180 --> 00:19:46,779
Just prepare ten million and we're good.

509
00:19:47,619 --> 00:19:48,319
I'm healthy enough.

510
00:19:48,599 --> 00:19:49,140
I just don't know if

511
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:50,380
your wallet's up to it, Lu.

512
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,440
Just as I thought.

513
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,019
Wait, where'd she go?

514
00:20:20,119 --> 00:20:20,759
Aren't you playing basketball?

515
00:20:20,779 --> 00:20:21,480
What are you dancing for?

516
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:21,880
Stop dancing.

517
00:20:22,839 --> 00:20:23,559
She left.

518
00:20:23,579 --> 00:20:24,779
That basketball guy just now,

519
00:20:24,799 --> 00:20:25,819
he was here with Xiaofang.

520
00:20:25,859 --> 00:20:26,420
She's gone.

521
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:27,319
I was keeping an eye out for you.

522
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:28,000
Don't worry, bro.

523
00:20:28,099 --> 00:20:28,740
Xiaofang didn't agree.

524
00:20:29,859 --> 00:20:30,519
Well, of course.

525
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:32,000
Bro, what are you

526
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,240
so smug about?

527
00:20:34,460 --> 00:20:35,400
At her pace,

528
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:36,059
finding the next guy

529
00:20:36,059 --> 00:20:37,140
is just a matter of days.

530
00:20:40,079 --> 00:20:40,660
Stop dancing.

531
00:20:45,259 --> 00:20:46,480
Why just sit here sighing?

532
00:20:46,619 --> 00:20:47,400
What else can I do?

533
00:20:47,779 --> 00:20:48,619
Just beat him up.

534
00:20:48,799 --> 00:20:49,720
Then no one in the village

535
00:20:49,740 --> 00:20:50,259
will dare mess with Xiaofang.

536
00:20:50,619 --> 00:20:51,619
So every guy she meets,

537
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:52,380
I beat up?

538
00:20:52,380 --> 00:20:53,720
How could I even live in this village?

539
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,700
No, bro, at this point,

540
00:20:55,740 --> 00:20:56,680
you can't afford to care about that.

541
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:57,339
Exactly.

542
00:20:57,819 --> 00:20:58,859
Your happiness for the rest of your life

543
00:20:58,880 --> 00:20:59,700
is about to slip away.

544
00:21:00,980 --> 00:21:01,960
Seems the ones my brother set up

545
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:02,960
aren't reliable either.

546
00:21:03,079 --> 00:21:04,440
This isn't looking for a wife.

547
00:21:04,559 --> 00:21:06,140
This is looking for a baby machine.

548
00:21:06,299 --> 00:21:07,079
Better let me handle it.

549
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:08,160
Second Auntie has picked out

550
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:09,539
a perfect one for you.

551
00:21:10,019 --> 00:21:10,900
Good-looking,

552
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:12,039
educated,

553
00:21:12,319 --> 00:21:13,460
low-maintenance, not bossy,

554
00:21:13,619 --> 00:21:14,579
obedient and loyal.

555
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:16,019
And most importantly,

556
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:17,720
rich.

557
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:24,559
Am I getting this right?

558
00:21:24,599 --> 00:21:26,059
You're my blind date?

559
00:21:26,759 --> 00:21:27,660
Sorry about that.

560
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:29,779
My son is a bit shy,

561
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:31,279
so I came to chat on his behalf.

562
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:36,660
No wonder you're a superstar mom.

563
00:21:37,079 --> 00:21:38,599
Full of ideas and boldness.

564
00:21:38,759 --> 00:21:40,799
Daring to think, act, and own it.

565
00:21:41,380 --> 00:21:43,180
I really love a personality like yours.

566
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:44,119
Just like me.

567
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,400
Xiaofang,

568
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,339
I'm very pleased with you.

569
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,099
As long as you're willing to marry in,

570
00:21:49,420 --> 00:21:50,519
a 200,000 yuan dowry,

571
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:51,859
transferred directly,

572
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:52,859
paid on the spot.

573
00:21:53,799 --> 00:21:54,119
Auntie,

574
00:21:54,119 --> 00:21:55,200
this is only our first meeting.

575
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:56,500
There's more.

576
00:21:57,019 --> 00:21:59,299
The car and house are fully paid off.

577
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:00,740
You can move right in.

578
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:01,500
And one of my shops,

579
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,519
I can give you one too.

580
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:03,359
I promise,

581
00:22:03,359 --> 00:22:04,640
your future good life

582
00:22:04,779 --> 00:22:06,319
will make everyone envious.

583
00:22:07,019 --> 00:22:07,359
Hold on,

584
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:09,220
even if you offer, I can't believe it.

585
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,079
We can sign a prenup

586
00:22:11,259 --> 00:22:12,019
and put all of this

587
00:22:12,099 --> 00:22:12,839
in writing.

588
00:22:14,539 --> 00:22:15,099
Sorry, but

589
00:22:15,099 --> 00:22:16,880
is your son unable to take care of himself?

590
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:17,720
No.

591
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:18,480
Infertile?

592
00:22:18,539 --> 00:22:19,700
Absolutely not.

593
00:22:21,559 --> 00:22:22,599
Way too old?

594
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:23,440
That's not it.

595
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,619
You look pretty young yourself.

596
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:25,519
Then what is it?

597
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:26,440
Stop guessing.

598
00:22:27,059 --> 00:22:28,079
Shijie is a great guy.

599
00:22:28,559 --> 00:22:29,660
He's very talented,

600
00:22:29,859 --> 00:22:31,519
clean, and has good taste.

601
00:22:31,819 --> 00:22:33,059
Keeps the house spotless,

602
00:22:33,119 --> 00:22:34,420
and dresses very sharply.

603
00:22:34,599 --> 00:22:36,380
He's really likable, very popular.

604
00:22:36,779 --> 00:22:37,559
I'm just worried

605
00:22:37,759 --> 00:22:39,319
he'll get led astray by the wrong crowd.

606
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:41,539
People say I'm too strict with him,

607
00:22:41,980 --> 00:22:42,819
that I've smothered him silly.

608
00:22:43,220 --> 00:22:44,200
Calling him a mama's boy and all.

609
00:22:44,599 --> 00:22:45,640
I don't think that's true.

610
00:22:46,039 --> 00:22:47,180
What right do they have to say that?

611
00:22:47,460 --> 00:22:49,059
I just want to find him

612
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,539
a girl I think is right for him.

613
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:54,559
Ma'am

614
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,920
I don't think

615
00:22:59,180 --> 00:22:59,839
this is right for me

616
00:23:02,299 --> 00:23:03,180
Well, think about it

617
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,019
If the man isn't home

618
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:06,500
and he just pays up

619
00:23:06,599 --> 00:23:07,460
what's the big deal?

620
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,059
Plenty of women

621
00:23:09,059 --> 00:23:10,380
would kill for this, okay?

622
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:12,500
Sis, only you

623
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:13,400
could live like that

624
00:23:14,119 --> 00:23:15,720
Everything you get for free

625
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:17,279
comes with a price tag attached

626
00:23:17,839 --> 00:23:18,720
If Xiaofang marries into that

627
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:19,680
who knows what she'll go through

628
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:22,259
Uncle really thinks ahead

629
00:23:22,779 --> 00:23:24,819
Let Uncle set you up instead

630
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,240
Someone reliable

631
00:23:27,339 --> 00:23:28,640
A top-tier corporate guy

632
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,079
From our hometown

633
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:31,400
He happens to be on

634
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,099
vacation and coming home

635
00:23:33,539 --> 00:23:34,700
I'll set up a meeting

636
00:23:35,839 --> 00:23:36,539
I've got a good feeling

637
00:23:39,039 --> 00:23:39,380
Meet him

638
00:23:39,859 --> 00:23:40,180
Meet him

639
00:23:40,839 --> 00:23:41,779
As we all know

640
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:43,640
The countryside of the past

641
00:23:43,799 --> 00:23:44,839
had limited functions

642
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:45,980
Idle resources

643
00:23:45,980 --> 00:23:47,000
Talent draining away

644
00:23:47,099 --> 00:23:48,339
But in today's society

645
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:50,740
demand for rural areas is exploding

646
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:54,400
City folks crave green mountains and clear waters

647
00:23:54,779 --> 00:23:55,660
Young people

648
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:57,140
have a burning passion for startups

649
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:58,400
You must be wondering

650
00:23:58,779 --> 00:24:00,279
why I'm meeting you like this today

651
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:01,119
What?

652
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:02,500
This is the age of efficiency

653
00:24:02,799 --> 00:24:03,839
My schedule's fully booked today

654
00:24:04,380 --> 00:24:05,559
During breaks in the lecture

655
00:24:05,859 --> 00:24:07,200
we can chat simultaneously

656
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:11,119
You're probably confused

657
00:24:11,519 --> 00:24:13,059
that I'd even agree to date you

658
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:14,680
Yeah

659
00:24:15,140 --> 00:24:16,380
When my uncle told me

660
00:24:16,380 --> 00:24:17,900
I almost cried tears of joy

661
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,119
Don't sell yourself too short

662
00:24:20,299 --> 00:24:21,799
I have my reasons for meeting you

663
00:24:22,319 --> 00:24:23,920
And you have your own value

664
00:24:25,980 --> 00:24:27,319
Me? I have value?

665
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:28,779
I thought I was just

666
00:24:28,779 --> 00:24:29,799
an ordinary person

667
00:24:30,079 --> 00:24:30,400
Exactly

668
00:24:30,779 --> 00:24:31,640
Your value

669
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,460
lies in being ordinary

670
00:24:36,319 --> 00:24:37,660
After you marry me

671
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:40,140
you'll come with me to the big city

672
00:24:40,579 --> 00:24:41,799
I can make money

673
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:42,599
but I don't have time

674
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:44,160
I need a woman

675
00:24:44,339 --> 00:24:46,059
to manage the household for me

676
00:24:46,319 --> 00:24:47,160
and take care of the kids

677
00:24:47,799 --> 00:24:48,799
Someone as outstanding as you

678
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:50,619
must have plenty of women

679
00:24:50,759 --> 00:24:51,819
willing to run your home and raise kids

680
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,200
lined up for you

681
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,079
But

682
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,000
none of them are cost-effective.

683
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,019
Some won't have kids

684
00:25:00,519 --> 00:25:02,200
Some want me to sacrifice my career

685
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:03,500
to boost their own

686
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:04,700
And some actually

687
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:05,799
make demands of me

688
00:25:06,079 --> 00:25:07,019
Isn't that ridiculous?

689
00:25:09,319 --> 00:25:10,059
Ridiculous

690
00:25:10,460 --> 00:25:11,680
But I think you're different

691
00:25:13,279 --> 00:25:14,079
Good-looking

692
00:25:14,579 --> 00:25:15,279
Presentable

693
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:16,579
Not vain

694
00:25:16,839 --> 00:25:17,819
And willing to have kids

695
00:25:19,079 --> 00:25:20,079
At the end of the day

696
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,579
I'm still a traditional good man

697
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,079
Dependable

698
00:25:24,599 --> 00:25:25,259
Responsible

699
00:25:26,259 --> 00:25:27,259
With a stable job

700
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:29,119
And plenty of earning power

701
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,640
Of course, I'm not pressuring you

702
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:32,000
You can occasionally

703
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:34,099
have afternoon tea

704
00:25:34,279 --> 00:25:35,640
get your nails done

705
00:25:35,940 --> 00:25:37,380
just like any housewife

706
00:25:37,759 --> 00:25:39,980
Take photos, post on social media

707
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:42,119
So everyone around you, friends

708
00:25:42,299 --> 00:25:42,740
and family

709
00:25:42,759 --> 00:25:44,059
will know how happy your life is

710
00:25:55,079 --> 00:25:55,640
This guy...

711
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,380
what does he actually look like?

712
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:00,819
I don't remember.

713
00:26:01,980 --> 00:26:03,200
He's such a great catch,

714
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:05,000
and you don't even remember

715
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:05,740
what he looks like?

716
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:07,619
It's not my fault.

717
00:26:07,759 --> 00:26:09,299
His face was like a blank mask.

718
00:26:09,299 --> 00:26:10,519
No features at all.

719
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:12,000
Xiaofang,

720
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,420
what on earth is going through your head?

721
00:26:15,619 --> 00:26:17,400
He's a big-city elite,

722
00:26:17,779 --> 00:26:19,019
has a car, has a house,

723
00:26:19,220 --> 00:26:20,099
and you're still being picky?

724
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:23,000
Well, why don't you go then?

725
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,180
You don't like this one,

726
00:26:25,180 --> 00:26:26,220
you don't fancy that one.

727
00:26:26,539 --> 00:26:28,559
What kind of guy are you even looking for?

728
00:26:30,960 --> 00:26:31,960
I don't really know.

729
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:33,859
I think there should be mutual respect,

730
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,079
mutual trust,

731
00:26:35,180 --> 00:26:36,079
comfort and ease.

732
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:38,579
Most importantly, we have to love ourselves first

733
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,039
before we can love someone else.

734
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:41,740
I can't quite explain it.

735
00:26:41,779 --> 00:26:43,200
It's about the feeling, Auntie.

736
00:26:43,740 --> 00:26:44,880
What the heck is "feeling"?

737
00:26:45,619 --> 00:26:46,579
Can it give you money to spend?

738
00:26:46,579 --> 00:26:47,680
Or raise your kids for you?

739
00:26:48,339 --> 00:26:49,259
Actually, I get exactly

740
00:26:49,259 --> 00:26:50,559
what our Fang'er just said.

741
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:51,880
Look at these guys.

742
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:52,960
Yao Jiahao,

743
00:26:53,259 --> 00:26:54,079
Carpenter Lu,

744
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:55,140
Boss Hao,

745
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:56,380
Shijie, Han Jun.

746
00:26:56,539 --> 00:26:57,880
They all show up wearing masks.

747
00:26:58,140 --> 00:26:58,900
You can't see their faces,

748
00:26:59,299 --> 00:27:00,259
and you can't see their hearts.

749
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:01,640
Speak plainly, would you?

750
00:27:03,799 --> 00:27:05,559
You're the only one who doesn't get plain talk.

751
00:27:06,079 --> 00:27:07,779
One's the guy you, Fanmei, like.

752
00:27:08,059 --> 00:27:09,619
One's the one Fanyan likes.

753
00:27:09,799 --> 00:27:11,740
One's the one you, Fanzhu, like.

754
00:27:12,119 --> 00:27:12,859
And another one

755
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:14,759
is the one Fanhu likes.

756
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,680
Is this even Xiaofang's matchmaking anymore?

757
00:27:17,079 --> 00:27:19,059
Aren't these all the ones you lot picked?

758
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,099
Our Xiaofang

759
00:27:21,359 --> 00:27:23,180
has to find someone she likes,

760
00:27:23,519 --> 00:27:24,039
right?

761
00:27:25,119 --> 00:27:26,220
If there's no feelings,

762
00:27:26,299 --> 00:27:27,240
then that's not called a match,

763
00:27:27,319 --> 00:27:27,700
"matching"...

764
00:27:29,420 --> 00:27:30,339
that's mating pigs!

765
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:44,380
Excuse me, coming through.

766
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:45,240
Coming through.

767
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:45,839
Take it slow.

768
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:46,599
Slow down, slow down.

769
00:27:47,079 --> 00:27:47,460
Slow down.

770
00:27:48,559 --> 00:27:49,140
Oh my goodness.

771
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,880
Careful, it's slippery.

772
00:27:54,759 --> 00:27:55,440
Huzi.

773
00:27:59,660 --> 00:28:00,859
Huanhuan.

774
00:28:01,420 --> 00:28:02,920
I haven't seen you in years.

775
00:28:03,079 --> 00:28:03,799
What brings you here?

776
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:05,039
Came back to see your mom.

777
00:28:06,099 --> 00:28:06,900
My husband...

778
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:09,579
passed away last year.

779
00:28:10,059 --> 00:28:11,339
Now it's just me.

780
00:28:11,599 --> 00:28:13,759
I figured, out there is just out there.

781
00:28:14,059 --> 00:28:15,119
Home is still best.

782
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:16,500
This is where my roots are, right?

783
00:28:16,819 --> 00:28:17,440
Right, right, right.

784
00:28:18,299 --> 00:28:19,059
Coming home feels grounded.

785
00:28:19,599 --> 00:28:20,099
Grounded.

786
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,640
How come I heard...

787
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:26,099
your Xiaofang's out on blind dates everywhere?

788
00:28:30,599 --> 00:28:31,539
Young folks these days...

789
00:28:31,539 --> 00:28:32,240
they're really bold.

790
00:28:32,799 --> 00:28:34,400
Way better than back in our day.

791
00:28:39,740 --> 00:28:40,299
What about you?

792
00:28:41,759 --> 00:28:42,799
Still on your own?

793
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,259
Okay.

794
00:28:52,599 --> 00:28:53,700
They're here, they're here!

795
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:56,380
It's the rule.

796
00:28:56,619 --> 00:28:58,059
No money, no getting out.

797
00:28:58,720 --> 00:28:59,940
No, no, no.

798
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:00,279
No.

799
00:29:00,519 --> 00:29:01,880
We've got the red envelopes ready.

800
00:29:02,039 --> 00:29:02,420
Besides...

801
00:29:02,599 --> 00:29:02,900
What's this?

802
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:04,019
You can't just raise the price now.

803
00:29:04,019 --> 00:29:04,819
Whose family, right before getting out...

804
00:29:04,819 --> 00:29:06,259
seems to be about the exit gift.

805
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:06,880
In-laws.

806
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:09,079
Our family's spent plenty too.

807
00:29:09,279 --> 00:29:10,579
Bought a house, bought a car.

808
00:29:10,740 --> 00:29:12,180
Just to get these two kids married.

809
00:29:12,319 --> 00:29:13,920
We've emptied out our savings.

810
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,920
You think raising a daughter costs nothing?

811
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,059
Still won't pay?

812
00:29:17,099 --> 00:29:18,220
Then forget the wedding.

813
00:29:18,460 --> 00:29:18,859
Wait, you...

814
00:29:19,319 --> 00:29:19,700
Xiao Zhu.

815
00:29:20,079 --> 00:29:20,519
Get out.

816
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:21,740
Are we having this wedding or not?

817
00:29:22,339 --> 00:29:22,940
Zhang Quan.

818
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:24,799
My mom had a tough time raising me too.

819
00:29:25,140 --> 00:29:26,160
Just give it to her, okay?

820
00:29:26,380 --> 00:29:26,700
Come on.

821
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:28,240
Didn't we already agree on this?

822
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:29,579
I'm begging you, alright?

823
00:29:29,799 --> 00:29:30,460
All these relatives are watching.

824
00:29:30,460 --> 00:29:30,859
Fine.

825
00:29:31,500 --> 00:29:32,000
Son.

826
00:29:32,559 --> 00:29:33,740
We're calling off this wedding.

827
00:29:33,940 --> 00:29:35,319
We're not buying a daughter-in-law.

828
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:35,799
Let's go.

829
00:29:36,460 --> 00:29:37,460
What the heck, you!

830
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:38,839
What are you even saying?

831
00:29:38,839 --> 00:29:39,980
Zhang Quan, are you a man or not?

832
00:29:40,019 --> 00:29:40,779
I am a man.

833
00:29:40,900 --> 00:29:41,980
What kind of attitude is this?

834
00:29:42,500 --> 00:29:43,920
Making me pay extra just to get out.

835
00:29:45,519 --> 00:29:46,160
I don't have money.

836
00:29:46,299 --> 00:29:47,700
Didn't I buy the house? The car?

837
00:29:47,740 --> 00:29:48,200
Shameless.

838
00:29:48,299 --> 00:29:48,920
I'm begging you.

839
00:29:49,259 --> 00:29:50,339
Please cut our family some slack.

840
00:29:50,339 --> 00:29:51,319
This is just a one-time thing for me.

841
00:29:51,319 --> 00:29:52,519
It's a once-in-a-lifetime thing!

842
00:29:52,599 --> 00:29:53,700
Then I'll go borrow it, okay?

843
00:29:53,819 --> 00:29:54,619
Once I borrow it, I'll give it to you.

844
00:29:54,619 --> 00:29:55,400
I want it now.

845
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:58,640
Let's talk this out nicely.

846
00:29:58,720 --> 00:29:59,700
What kind of attitude is that?

847
00:30:03,420 --> 00:30:04,779
I was following Xiaochao at the time

848
00:30:04,779 --> 00:30:05,839
And we ran over to that

849
00:30:05,839 --> 00:30:06,640
front entrance of the hotel

850
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:07,480
I wanted to go see them

851
00:30:07,740 --> 00:30:08,140
And then, you know

852
00:30:08,380 --> 00:30:09,880
I saw two groups start fighting

853
00:30:10,059 --> 00:30:11,880
Xiaozhu with her mom and dad

854
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,599
were on this side

855
00:30:12,599 --> 00:30:13,440
And on the other side was

856
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:14,960
Zhang Quan with his mom and dad

857
00:30:15,059 --> 00:30:16,059
And this side was yelling

858
00:30:16,319 --> 00:30:17,220
Get out of the car! Get out!

859
00:30:17,220 --> 00:30:18,160
I won't! My daughter!

860
00:30:18,279 --> 00:30:19,640
So what happened next?

861
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:21,160
In the end, they paid up

862
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:22,119
They paid up

863
00:30:22,140 --> 00:30:23,660
Xiaozhu got out only after getting the money

864
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,599
I watched them up on the stage

865
00:30:26,099 --> 00:30:26,839
"I love you"

866
00:30:27,039 --> 00:30:27,819
"I do"

867
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,200
It was so weird

868
00:30:31,099 --> 00:30:32,160
That's just what you think

869
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:34,059
Don't believe me? Ask Xiaozhu in a few days

870
00:30:34,259 --> 00:30:36,319
Those two will keep living just fine

871
00:30:36,660 --> 00:30:38,279
Sure, on the surface life goes on

872
00:30:38,279 --> 00:30:39,559
But won't it bother them deep down?

873
00:30:40,900 --> 00:30:43,440
It's like a nail hammered into a wall

874
00:30:43,700 --> 00:30:44,759
Pull out the nail

875
00:30:44,799 --> 00:30:46,279
and that hole in the wall

876
00:30:46,380 --> 00:30:47,539
will always be there

877
00:30:47,799 --> 00:30:49,640
Yes, that's exactly what I mean

878
00:30:49,740 --> 00:30:50,180
Grandma

879
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,720
you totally speak my mind

880
00:30:54,779 --> 00:30:55,859
People were poor in the past

881
00:30:56,019 --> 00:30:57,220
Feelings were pure

882
00:30:57,700 --> 00:30:58,839
Now people are rich

883
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:00,839
And everything has a price tag

884
00:31:01,599 --> 00:31:03,779
Money's become the basis of marriage

885
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:06,660
And love has transformed

886
00:31:07,299 --> 00:31:09,000
into a luxury item

887
00:31:10,059 --> 00:31:11,799
Why are you learning from Yang Fanzhu too?

888
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,559
Never talking like a normal person all day

889
00:31:14,140 --> 00:31:15,700
Auntie, you're amazing

890
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:17,480
Those are Master Fanzhu's exact quotes

891
00:31:18,819 --> 00:31:19,740
Listen, Xiaofang

892
00:31:19,759 --> 00:31:21,240
Can you stop running your mouth?

893
00:31:21,759 --> 00:31:23,700
You've been willful enough already

894
00:31:24,559 --> 00:31:25,859
After so many blind dates

895
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:26,920
You haven't liked a single one

896
00:31:27,420 --> 00:31:29,599
At least pick one for us, would you?

897
00:31:29,779 --> 00:31:30,460
Right?

898
00:31:31,039 --> 00:31:32,920
My dad secretly told me yesterday

899
00:31:33,079 --> 00:31:33,819
There's no rush

900
00:31:34,079 --> 00:31:34,660
He'll support me

901
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:36,859
He's the one who spoiled her

902
00:31:37,380 --> 00:31:38,799
What's most important in marriage?

903
00:31:38,940 --> 00:31:39,279
Fanmei

904
00:31:39,599 --> 00:31:40,579
You tell her

905
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:41,900
Money

906
00:31:42,700 --> 00:31:44,160
She shouldn't have asked you in the first place

907
00:31:44,359 --> 00:31:45,779
You're really obsessed with money

908
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,480
Even the husband you want is surnamed "Money"

909
00:31:48,779 --> 00:31:49,359
If you ask me

910
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:51,119
All men in this world are the same

911
00:31:52,059 --> 00:31:53,819
All crows under heaven are equally black

912
00:31:54,539 --> 00:31:55,140
Grandma

913
00:31:56,140 --> 00:31:57,460
Auntie says Grandpa is a crow

914
00:31:57,759 --> 00:31:58,920
Says he's as black as a crow

915
00:31:59,619 --> 00:32:00,400
That's a lie!

916
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:02,259
That's not right

917
00:32:02,619 --> 00:32:03,559
Your grandpa

918
00:32:03,839 --> 00:32:06,319
has genuinely cool, pale skin

919
00:32:57,519 --> 00:32:58,759
The lantern paper for our ancestors

920
00:32:59,099 --> 00:33:00,119
It can't fall into the river

921
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:01,680
Good thing I fished it out for you

922
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:03,380
The ink's all smudged now

923
00:33:06,099 --> 00:33:07,400
I threw it in on purpose

924
00:33:09,140 --> 00:33:10,180
You were gonna throw it away anyway

925
00:33:16,579 --> 00:33:17,799
Why toss it into the river?

926
00:33:18,940 --> 00:33:20,460
"Madam Zhou of the Qu family"

927
00:33:22,119 --> 00:33:23,799
My grandma didn't even deserve a name

928
00:33:24,660 --> 00:33:25,859
Might as well toss it in the river

929
00:33:28,220 --> 00:33:28,900
Same with my mom

930
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:33,880
Her tombstone reads,

931
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:34,700
"Madam Wang of the Yang family"

932
00:33:36,119 --> 00:33:37,119
But I remember her name

933
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:40,039
Before she passed, she told me

934
00:33:40,740 --> 00:33:42,539
she secretly carved her name on a big tree

935
00:33:42,799 --> 00:33:43,980
And told me not to forget her

936
00:33:45,099 --> 00:33:45,900
But I feel that as long as

937
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:46,900
I think of her, remember her

938
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:48,759
she'll always be here

939
00:33:50,380 --> 00:33:51,019
So then

940
00:33:51,859 --> 00:33:52,859
What was her name?

941
00:33:54,940 --> 00:33:55,660
Xiuhe

942
00:34:01,220 --> 00:34:01,920
And your grandma?

943
00:34:03,259 --> 00:34:04,119
My grandma's name is

944
00:34:05,579 --> 00:34:06,259
Zhou Yunfang

945
00:34:10,420 --> 00:34:11,199
Do you have a pen?

946
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:12,760
Yeah

947
00:34:13,699 --> 00:34:15,420
Let's write their names

948
00:34:15,559 --> 00:34:16,400
on the lantern paper

949
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:20,539
Okay

950
00:34:29,039 --> 00:34:30,519
So you gather herbs

951
00:34:31,539 --> 00:34:31,880
Yeah

952
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,599
Dad, Mom.

953
00:35:10,380 --> 00:35:11,579
You... you stubborn girl!

954
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:12,940
The lantern slips the whole family was waiting for,

955
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:13,699
and you just grabbed them?

956
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:22,639
This child of mine...

957
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:24,900
Why are you so stubborn?

958
00:35:25,420 --> 00:35:27,000
You won't even follow the ancestors' rules.

959
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,380
The coarse cloth Grandma wove

960
00:35:28,639 --> 00:35:29,380
is still buried at the bottom of the chest.

961
00:35:29,579 --> 00:35:30,639
Why can't she have a name on it?

962
00:35:31,380 --> 00:35:31,800
Besides,

963
00:35:32,199 --> 00:35:33,199
we float these river lanterns

964
00:35:33,739 --> 00:35:34,920
so that those who've passed on

965
00:35:35,179 --> 00:35:36,440
are remembered and missed, right?

966
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:37,960
If you don't write it, and I don't write it,

967
00:35:38,519 --> 00:35:40,019
who's going to remember them later?

968
00:35:47,260 --> 00:35:47,679
Well,

969
00:35:49,619 --> 00:35:50,760
the child does have a point.

970
00:35:51,500 --> 00:35:52,139
Fine, fine.

971
00:35:52,599 --> 00:35:53,519
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

972
00:35:54,639 --> 00:35:55,099
Come on, come on.

973
00:35:56,460 --> 00:35:57,260
Dad, Mom,

974
00:35:57,860 --> 00:35:58,579
don't forget:

975
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:00,480
my grandma's name is Zhou Yunfang.

976
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:02,119
We remember.

977
00:36:46,019 --> 00:36:46,539
Thank you.

978
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:47,960
This...

979
00:36:48,300 --> 00:36:49,719
is prickly pear wine I brewed myself.

980
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:54,400
I'm the one who should thank you.

981
00:36:58,739 --> 00:36:59,719
That day...

982
00:37:00,039 --> 00:37:01,460
your grandpa really...

983
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:03,360
crashed straight into my heart.

984
00:37:05,579 --> 00:37:06,880
Love at first sight?

985
00:37:09,139 --> 00:37:10,119
Your grandpa and I,

986
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:12,559
it really was love at first sight.

987
00:37:15,679 --> 00:37:16,219
Xiaofang,

988
00:37:16,539 --> 00:37:17,860
when your grandma was young,

989
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:19,139
she especially loved flowers.

990
00:37:19,679 --> 00:37:21,360
Every time grandpa came down the mountain,

991
00:37:21,820 --> 00:37:23,840
he'd pick lots of wildflowers for grandma.

992
00:37:25,619 --> 00:37:26,079
Right?

993
00:37:29,539 --> 00:37:30,179
No wonder!

994
00:37:30,179 --> 00:37:31,260
That's why my dad always

995
00:37:31,260 --> 00:37:32,539
brings home a bouquet of flowers.

996
00:37:33,460 --> 00:37:34,719
Your dad takes after grandpa.

997
00:37:34,820 --> 00:37:35,440
Deep down,

998
00:37:35,719 --> 00:37:36,780
they're both romantics.

999
00:37:37,239 --> 00:37:37,679
That's right.

1000
00:37:38,219 --> 00:37:40,079
For a while, I kept waking up from nightmares.

1001
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:41,420
Dad would hold me,

1002
00:37:42,300 --> 00:37:43,340
and in his arms,

1003
00:37:43,940 --> 00:37:45,239
smelling his scent,

1004
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,000
I felt so safe.

1005
00:37:47,460 --> 00:37:48,860
Sometimes when I think back now,

1006
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:50,699
I feel like I can still smell

1007
00:37:51,159 --> 00:37:52,980
that faint scent on him.

1008
00:37:53,940 --> 00:37:54,420
Grandma,

1009
00:37:55,139 --> 00:37:56,420
did grandpa ever say

1010
00:37:56,420 --> 00:37:57,000
he loved you?

1011
00:37:58,940 --> 00:38:00,079
He did say he loved me.

1012
00:38:01,619 --> 00:38:02,320
Mom,

1013
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:04,199
in your generation,

1014
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:05,800
who ever talked about love?

1015
00:38:06,820 --> 00:38:07,280
Besides,

1016
00:38:07,519 --> 00:38:08,940
I've never heard my dad say it.

1017
00:38:11,719 --> 00:38:12,599
Your dad,

1018
00:38:12,980 --> 00:38:14,980
he did tell me he loved me.

1019
00:38:15,539 --> 00:38:16,960
When I married him,

1020
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:18,559
he told me

1021
00:38:19,119 --> 00:38:20,579
he'd love me forever.

1022
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:22,820
Then when I had you,

1023
00:38:23,179 --> 00:38:24,360
he told me again,

1024
00:38:24,860 --> 00:38:27,199
"I'll love you and our child forever."

1025
00:38:28,159 --> 00:38:29,519
Then when we had you too,

1026
00:38:30,019 --> 00:38:30,880
he said again,

1027
00:38:31,159 --> 00:38:34,500
"I'll love you and the kids forever."

1028
00:38:37,380 --> 00:38:38,440
Your dad,

1029
00:38:38,559 --> 00:38:41,019
in front of you kids,

1030
00:38:41,039 --> 00:38:42,659
he's always so serious.

1031
00:38:44,019 --> 00:38:45,860
But when it's just him and me,

1032
00:38:47,619 --> 00:38:49,199
he's shameless.

1033
00:38:49,559 --> 00:38:51,300
He'll say anything.

1034
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:53,840
Mom,

1035
00:38:54,099 --> 00:38:56,260
That's dad sweet-talking you.

1036
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,579
Dad's spoiled you rotten.

1037
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:00,699
That's right.

1038
00:39:00,699 --> 00:39:02,480
I'm so blessed.

1039
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:04,599
That's what love is.

1040
00:39:04,599 --> 00:39:05,840
Come on, mom, have a drink.

1041
00:39:06,019 --> 00:39:07,099
I want to be just like grandma,

1042
00:39:07,179 --> 00:39:08,599
and let love come crashing in on its own.

1043
00:39:33,619 --> 00:39:36,000
By the time Xiaofang's baby is born,

1044
00:39:36,699 --> 00:39:39,840
the new prickly pear wine will be ready to drink.

1045
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:43,000
Flowers bloom, leaves fall,

1046
00:39:43,579 --> 00:39:45,280
and the little puppy grows up.

1047
00:39:47,159 --> 00:39:49,460
That's when you realize how fast time flies.

1048
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:52,840
But love is different when it comes.

1049
00:39:53,460 --> 00:39:55,539
You just know, right away.

1050
00:39:59,500 --> 00:39:59,960
Mom.

1051
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,000
Do you still miss Dad?

1052
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:11,900
Hasn't he always been with me?

1053
00:40:15,519 --> 00:40:16,179
No, no, no.

1054
00:40:25,619 --> 00:40:28,019
Leaving isn't the end.

1055
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:30,300
Being forgotten is.

1056
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,420
The memories of your dad in my heart,

1057
00:40:36,460 --> 00:40:37,920
there are just so many.

1058
00:40:43,320 --> 00:40:45,400
Do you think these river lanterns we set out,

1059
00:40:45,599 --> 00:40:46,619
will they receive them?

1060
00:40:47,420 --> 00:40:47,860
They will.

1061
00:40:49,059 --> 00:40:50,280
It's not scary when someone passes away.

1062
00:40:51,519 --> 00:40:52,840
Being completely forgotten,

1063
00:40:55,199 --> 00:40:56,199
that's when they're truly gone.

1064
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,139
What's your name?

1065
00:41:07,739 --> 00:41:08,440
I'm Yang Shu.

1066
00:41:09,719 --> 00:41:10,460
Shu, as in a big tree.

1067
00:41:15,239 --> 00:41:15,719
And you?

1068
00:41:17,940 --> 00:41:18,699
Qu Manxia.

1069
00:41:19,159 --> 00:41:19,820
Man, as in stretching out.

1070
00:41:20,260 --> 00:41:21,019
Xia, as in rosy clouds.

1071
00:41:33,960 --> 00:41:34,480
Mom.

1072
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:34,920
Cheer up.

1073
00:41:35,099 --> 00:41:36,039
Don't cry, don't cry.

1074
00:41:36,699 --> 00:41:37,260
Be happy.

1075
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:38,500
It's okay, be happy.

1076
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:52,940
Be happy.

1077
00:42:03,599 --> 00:42:04,679
Turns out love

1078
00:42:04,719 --> 00:42:05,920
isn't rushing to pair up,

1079
00:42:07,719 --> 00:42:09,679
nor is it what others say is a good match.

1080
00:42:12,119 --> 00:42:13,579
It's like Grandpa and Grandma,

1081
00:42:14,139 --> 00:42:14,840
walking slowly,

1082
00:42:15,219 --> 00:42:16,000
loving deeply.

1083
00:43:03,059 --> 00:43:04,320
Be gentle, gentle, gentle.

1084
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:07,280
Don't push so hard, okay?

1085
00:43:07,280 --> 00:43:08,139
You'll squeeze the baby out.

1086
00:43:08,199 --> 00:43:09,239
I didn't.

1087
00:43:10,139 --> 00:43:11,579
I'm just listening for movement.

1088
00:43:11,579 --> 00:43:13,079
Why are you talking nonsense?

1089
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:15,860
Look how rough you are.

1090
00:43:16,099 --> 00:43:17,500
How am I rough?

1091
00:43:24,300 --> 00:43:24,860
Doctor.

1092
00:43:25,579 --> 00:43:26,639
Is this...

1093
00:43:26,940 --> 00:43:28,519
Looks like a boy, doesn't it?

1094
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:30,000
The baby in her belly

1095
00:43:30,340 --> 00:43:32,260
is your leverage.

1096
00:43:32,260 --> 00:43:33,320
Once you have him,

1097
00:43:33,619 --> 00:43:34,860
you won't feel insecure.

1098
00:43:35,159 --> 00:43:36,480
I only have one wish now.

1099
00:43:36,980 --> 00:43:38,239
The Yang family bloodline

1100
00:43:38,579 --> 00:43:39,619
can't end with me.

1101
00:43:39,639 --> 00:43:40,380
It just can't be cut off.

1102
00:43:40,579 --> 00:43:41,139
Xiaofang.

1103
00:43:42,019 --> 00:43:42,519
Eat more.

1104
00:43:42,739 --> 00:43:44,059
You're the big hero here.

1105
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:45,699
Xiaofang is so young.

1106
00:43:45,699 --> 00:43:47,019
She'll definitely remarry someday.

1107
00:43:47,099 --> 00:43:48,940
But having a kid is such a hassle.

1108
00:43:49,440 --> 00:43:50,880
Ever thought about giving the kid up?

1109
00:43:51,460 --> 00:43:53,219
This Shu guy is definitely shady.

